    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-13T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">974.531/7–1351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DAC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d411fn1">Repeated for information to Cairo, London, Amman,
                        Baghdad, Beirut, Damascus, Jidda, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-13T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 13, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Emb believes US can ill-afford take other than forthright stand on such an
                    important issue as restrictions by Egypt on Suez Canal traffic. Without attempt
                    review gen considerations, I mention only one of local application: Since we
                    sponsored May 18 res sharply critical of Israel and may find it necessary join
                    in criticizing Israel further re implementation ref res, it becomes important
                    that we be no less critical of Egypt in present case.</p>
                <p>Emb believes moreover that merits case fully justify strong position and that
                    para 3 <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 14, July 9<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d411fn2">Same as telegram 17 to New York, <ref target="#pg_756">p.
                            756</ref>.</note> does not go far enough altho our <pb facs="0808"
                        n="768" xml:id="pg_768"/> emphasis may well be on Point IV BIE restrictions
                    as they affect US interest and rights other <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    members in order more readily refute charges action merely evidence pro-Israel
                    policy. From standpoint US interests as viewed from this mission, Emb agrees
                    with opinion Brit <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> as reported London
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 226, July 11<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d411fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_763">p. 763</ref>.</note> to
                    Dept that weight our co-sponsorship needed to realize maximum result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
